The foot (standard symbol: ft) is a unit of length in the British imperial and United States customary systems of measurement.

results.t: What is Foot? Definition, Examples, Facts
results.p: A foot is a unit to measure the length or distance in the US. “Foot” refers to a single unit of measurement whereas “feet” is its plural alternative.
Aug 20, 2024 — Foot, in measurement, any of numerous ancient, medieval, and modern linear measures (commonly 25 to 34 cm) based on the length of the human foot.
